params.data: Array of typed rebalance data struct (fleet commander address used as fromArk)

approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `value` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

decimals().details: Decimals are computed by adding the decimal offset on top of the underlying asset's decimals. This "original" value is cached during construction of the vault contract. If this read operation fails (e.g., the asset has not been created yet), a default of 18 is used to represent the underlying asset's decimals. See {IERC20Metadata-decimals}.

returns._0: The estimated amount of accrued tips

forceRebalance((address,address,uint256).details: has no cooldown enforced but only callable by privileged role

params.data: Array of typed rebalance data struct

params.assets: The amount of assets to forcefully withdraw
params.owner: The address of the owner of the assets
params.receiver: The address that will receive the withdrawn assets

returns._0: The amount of assets forcefully withdrawn

params.owner: The address of the owner of the assets

mint(uint256,address).details: See {IERC4626-mint}. As opposed to {deposit}, minting is allowed even if the vault is in a state where the price of a share is zero. In this case, the shares will be minted without requiring any assets to be deposited.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

params.data: Array of typed rebalance data struct

params.ark: The address of the Ark to remove

setTipRate(uint256).details: The tip rate is set as a Percentage. Percentages use 18 decimals of precision      For example, for a 5% rate, you'd pass 5 * 1e18 (5 000 000 000 000 000 000)

params.newTipRate: The new tip rate as a Percentage

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `value`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `value`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `value`.

params.newCooldown: The new cooldown period in seconds

arks(uint256).notice: Retrieves the ark address at the specified index

emergencyShutdown().notice: Initiates an emergency shutdown of the FleetCommander

estimateAccruedTip().notice: Estimates the amount of tips accrued since the last tip accrual

forceWithdraw(uint256,address,address).notice: Forces a withdrawal of assets from the FleetCommander

getArks().notice: Retrieves the arks currently linked to fleet

isArkActive(address).notice: Checks if the ark is part of the fleet

lastTipTimestamp().notice: The timestamp of the last tip accrual

maxForceWithdraw(address).notice: Returns the maximum amount of the underlying asset that can be withdrawn from the owner balance in the Vault, through a force withdraw call.

setMaxAllocation(address,uint256).notice: Sets a new maximum allocation for an Ark

setTipJar().notice: Sets a new tip jar address

tipJar().notice: The address where accrued tips are sent
